<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,284,790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[312,443,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<emphasis box="[632,747,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">argenteus</emphasis>
“silvery” in reference to the stout whitish orange setae that cover the mesosomal dorsum, which appear silvery at certain angles.
</paragraph>
